Studio XX is pleased to host artist Kimura Byol with PROJECT #6261 MONTR&Eacute;AL, from August 25th to October 9th, 2016, as part of our 2016-17 residency program.&nbsp;




During the Studio XX artist residency (August 25th to October 9th), kimura byol-nathalie lemoine will make a non-linear narrative and interactive film (Korsakow).&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&quot;With this residency at Studio XX, I will explore the possibilities of non-linear narrative and interactive film with the software Korsakow as a playful and participative web-documentary.

This project incorporates the particular reality of Montreal&rsquo;s local street address system, which differs from other realities which are familiar to me, such as those of Belgium where I was adopted and South Korea where I was born. I had the idea to use my adoption number (#6261) to get to know the new city (where I wanted to immigrate) through meeting with the inhabitants of that street number.

I gave myself a structure of 100 days to work from this concept.I randomly chose 100 streets and sent a call to participation to those selected addresses. &nbsp;I visited the city by foot and public transportation, carrying only my camera to conform/inform the existence of the number #6261and to document the investigation process and meetings.

I had the privilege of discovering different social, ethnic, economic and linguistic realities.&quot;

&nbsp;

Illustration : Eloisa Aquino

